d issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm looking at an interesting git diff for the test class, and it seems like the file was tracked from a previous user. Maybe our initial write got tracked somehow? I should add resources not shown in the diff since they're untracked. Is “git diff --no-index” necessary? It’s something to consider. I'm also noting potential issues with native build arguments and metadata reachability. I’m wondering if the inner private class will be accounted for in the native-image. Overall, there’s a lot to keep track of here!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating test conditions and metadata**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering whether new strict tests might fail if the runtime isn't HotSpot, especially since the project is likely using GraalVM JDK 21. There's a developer rule about not using reflection directly in tests unless the public API requires it, which we don’t. I’m also thinking about whether adding reflective metadata for java.util.EnumSet might fail validation since it's a java.* type. \\\\n\\\\nAdditionally, I'll need to clarify if the required metadata files, like reflect-config.json or reachability-metadata, are properly configured and if the TCK includes these resources. It’s all quite detailed!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Refined the active-class coverage for `ClassUtil$EnumTypeLocator`.\\n\\nChanges made:\\n- Updated `ClassUtilInnerEnumTypeLocatorTest` to assert successful enum type resolution for:\\n  - Empty `EnumSet`\\n  - Empty `EnumMap`\\n- Added JVM/native module access for `java.util` in:\\n  - `tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build.gradle`\\n- Added test-only native-image reflection metadata for the JDK enum container fields used by Jackson:\\n  - `tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`\\n\\nThis should allow `EnumTypeLocator.get(...)` to execute `Field#get(Object)` successfully instead of 